Here's the map of what lives where — everything under artifacts/ is what you'd edit:

Web app (artifacts/anchored/)

src/pages/ — each screen (dashboard, anchors, proof, settings, onboarding, login)
src/components/ — reusable pieces (AnchorCard, VoiceSheet, TutorialOverlay, etc.)
src/lib/ — data layer (Supabase storage, auth, language/i18n)
src/App.tsx — app shell and routing
Mobile app (artifacts/mobile/)

app/(tabs)/ — the four tab screens
app/ — other screens (onboarding, proof detail)
components/ — shared mobile components
lib/ — same data layer mirroring the web
Backend (artifacts/api-server/)

src/routes/ — API endpoints (file uploads, receipts)
Shared config

pnpm-workspace.yaml — package setup
supabase/migrations/ — database schema (applied in Supabase dashboard)
Things you don't need to touch

node_modules/ — not in GitHub (run pnpm install to restore them)
artifacts/anchored/src/components/ui/ — shadcn auto-generated UI primitives
.agents/ — Replit agent memory, not app code
To run it on another machine after cloning:

pnpm install          # restore dependencies
pnpm --filter @workspace/anchored run dev    # web
pnpm --filter @workspace/mobile run dev      # mobile
pnpm --filter @workspace/api-server run dev  # backend

You'll also need to copy over the environment variables (Supabase URL/key, session secret) — those aren't in GitHub for security reasons.
